assertion_line: 81
expression: "loom_help(&[\"msg\"])"
---
Resolve outstanding `loom:clarify` and `loom:blocked` beads

Usage: loom msg [OPTIONS]

Options:
  -w, --workspace <PATH>  Workspace root. Defaults to the current working directory
  -A, --agent <BACKEND>   Override the agent backend for this invocation [possible values: claude, pi]
  -h, --help              Print help

Workflow:
  -s, --spec <LABEL>  Filter to a specific spec label
  -n, --number <N>    Select bead by 1-based index in the printed list. Mutually exclusive with `-b`
  -b, --bead <ID>     Select bead by id. Mutually exclusive with `-n`
  -o, --option <INT>  Fast-reply with the body of `### Option <int>` for a clarify bead. Validated — missing subsection exits non-zero before any bd state is mutated. Mutually exclusive with `-r` and `-d`
  -r, --reply <TEXT>  Fast-reply with verbatim text. Works on any bead regardless of whether it has an `## Options` section. Mutually exclusive with `-o` and `-d`
  -d, --dismiss       Dismiss the bead (write canonical note + remove the loom:* label)
